## Database Schema

### Table 1 — `mot_failure_priors`
Source of truth for base fault rates. Populated from DVSA public MOT data.

```sql
CREATE TABLE mot_failure_priors (
    id              UUID PRIMARY KEY DEFAULT gen_random_uuid(),
    make            VARCHAR(100) NOT NULL,
    model           VARCHAR(100) NOT NULL,
    year_band_start INTEGER NOT NULL,
    year_band_end   INTEGER NOT NULL,
    mileage_band    VARCHAR(50),        -- '0-50k' | '50k-100k' | '100k-150k' | '150k+'
    fault_category  VARCHAR(100) NOT NULL, -- 'brakes' | 'engine' | 'suspension' | 'electrical'
    fault_type      VARCHAR(100) NOT NULL, -- normalised fault_type matching our vocabulary
    failure_rate    DECIMAL(5,4) NOT NULL, -- 0.0000–1.0000
    sample_size     INTEGER NOT NULL,
    source          VARCHAR(50) DEFAULT 'dvsa_mot',
    last_updated    TIMESTAMP WITH TIME ZONE DEFAULT NOW(),
    UNIQUE(make, model, year_band_start, year_band_end, mileage_band, fault_type)
);
```

### Table 2 — `listing_fault_outcomes`
Every fault prediction we make, with ground truth populated over time.

```sql
CREATE TABLE listing_fault_outcomes (
    id              UUID PRIMARY KEY DEFAULT gen_random_uuid(),
    listing_id      UUID REFERENCES listings(id) ON DELETE CASCADE,

    -- vehicle snapshot at time of detection
    make            VARCHAR(100),
    model           VARCHAR(100),
    year            INTEGER,
    mileage         INTEGER,
    fuel_type       VARCHAR(50),

    -- AI prediction
    predicted_fault_type    VARCHAR(100) NOT NULL,
    predicted_confidence    DECIMAL(4,3),
    predicted_severity      VARCHAR(50),
    ai_overall_confidence   DECIMAL(4,3),

    -- ground truth (populated later)
    confirmed       BOOLEAN,        -- NULL=unverified | TRUE=correct | FALSE=wrong
    actual_fault_type   VARCHAR(100), -- if confirmed=FALSE and real fault known
    confirmed_at    TIMESTAMP WITH TIME ZONE,
    confirmed_by    VARCHAR(50),    -- 'user_feedback' | 'manual'

    created_at      TIMESTAMP WITH TIME ZONE DEFAULT NOW()
);

CREATE INDEX idx_fault_outcomes_make_model 
    ON listing_fault_outcomes(make, model, year, mileage);
CREATE INDEX idx_fault_outcomes_fault_type 
    ON listing_fault_outcomes(predicted_fault_type);
CREATE INDEX idx_fault_outcomes_confirmed 
    ON listing_fault_outcomes(confirmed);
```

### Table 3 — `fault_probability_cache`
Precomputed posteriors. Rebuilt nightly. What the pipeline actually queries at runtime.

```sql
CREATE TABLE fault_probability_cache (
    id              UUID PRIMARY KEY DEFAULT gen_random_uuid(),
    make            VARCHAR(100) NOT NULL,
    model           VARCHAR(100),
    year_band_start INTEGER,
    year_band_end   INTEGER,
    mileage_band    VARCHAR(50),
    fault_type      VARCHAR(100) NOT NULL,
    fault_category  VARCHAR(100),
    probability     DECIMAL(5,4) NOT NULL,
    prior_sample_size   INTEGER,
    observed_count      INTEGER,
    confirmed_count     INTEGER,
    confidence_in_prob  VARCHAR(20), -- 'high' | 'medium' | 'low'
    computed_at     TIMESTAMP WITH TIME ZONE DEFAULT NOW(),
    UNIQUE(make, model, year_band_start, year_band_end, mileage_band, fault_type)
);
```

