## Bayesian Update Logic (Nightly Job)

```python
# P(fault | vehicle) using Laplace smoothing

def compute_posterior(
    make: str, model: str, 
    year_band: tuple, mileage_band: str, 
    fault_type: str
) -> float:
    
    prior = get_mot_prior(make, model, year_band, mileage_band, fault_type)
    observed = get_listing_outcomes(make, model, year_band, mileage_band, fault_type)
    
    # Laplace smoothing — prevents zero probabilities on unseen combinations
    alpha = 1
    
    prior_failures = (prior.failure_rate * prior.sample_size) if prior else 0
    prior_total = prior.sample_size if prior else 0
    
    # Only use confirmed observations — unverified don't update the posterior
    confirmed_failures = observed.confirmed_true_count
    confirmed_total = observed.confirmed_total
    
    posterior = (prior_failures + confirmed_failures + alpha) / \
                (prior_total + confirmed_total + 2 * alpha)
    
    return round(posterior, 4)
```

