## How It Integrates with the Detection Pipeline

### Today (Step 3):
```python
known_faults = session.query(CarsCommonProblem)\
    .filter_by(make=make, model=model).all()
```

### With Bayesian layer (Step 3 upgraded):
```python
probable_faults = session.query(FaultProbabilityCache)\
    .filter_by(make=make, model=model)\
    .filter(FaultProbabilityCache.year_band_start <= year)\
    .filter(FaultProbabilityCache.year_band_end >= year)\
    .filter(FaultProbabilityCache.mileage_band == derive_mileage_band(mileage))\
    .filter(FaultProbabilityCache.probability >= 0.15)\
    .order_by(FaultProbabilityCache.probability.desc())\
    .limit(5)\
    .all()
```

These are passed into the AI prompt as informed context:

```
STATISTICALLY PROBABLE FAULTS FOR THIS VEHICLE:
Based on {sample_size} real UK vehicles of this type:
- timing_chain_failure: 31% of BMW 3 Series 2010-2015 with >150k miles
- brake_calipers_rear: 23% of Vauxhall Astra 2010-2014 with 100k-150k miles

Assess whether the above are present or can be ruled out based on the 
listing title and description. Also identify any additional faults.
```

