## DVSA MOT Data

**Source:** https://data.gov.uk/dataset/e3939ef8-30c7-4ca8-9c7c-ad9475cc9b2f/anonymised-mot-tests-and-results

**What it contains:** ~40 million anonymised MOT tests per year. Each record includes make, model, year, mileage at test, test result (pass/fail), and reason codes for each failure item.

**Why it matters:** This is millions of verified real-world fault observations, freely available. It gives us statistically robust priors before we've processed a single eBay listing ourselves.

**Ingestion approach:**
1. Download annual CSV (filtered to cars, ~15GB raw → ~2GB filtered)
2. Map DVSA reason codes to our normalised `fault_type` vocabulary
3. Aggregate failure rates per make/model/year_band/mileage_band
4. Insert into `mot_failure_priors`
5. Trigger a full `fault_probability_cache` rebuild

This is a significant one-off task but transformative for detection quality. Planned for a future phase once the core pipeline is stable.

